        "lineStyle": "solid",
        "effectOuterShadow": true,
        "fontFamily": "Verdana",
        "fontSize": 10,
        "textColor": "#000000",
        "label": "If you click on the space below the heading “Vendor Lookup” a drop down menu of company names and numbers will appear.  You may search through these entries by using the blue slider on the right side of the window or you can enter the first letter of the company name to progress you to those company’s that start with that letter.  Then use the slider from there to find the company you are looking for.  After you have found the company, simply click on the name and the system will automatically load the information for that company into the purchase order screen.\n\nThe Company name and address will appear below the vendor number window and the current date will automatically be loaded into the field “Order Date” \n\nThe bill to address is a fixed set of information that should not be altered.  The Ship to Address is automatically filled in by the system with the same information as the Bill To address.  If needed, this address may be altered to reflect an alternative address if you need the items you are ordering need to go to a job site or client address or such.",
        "ddrArrangeOrder": 12
      },
      "type": "label"
    },
